Food Facilities Violations

This web page contains the most recent inspection information for approximately 800 food facilities permitted in the City of Berkeley. These include restaurants, bars, grocery stores, markets, mobile food facilities, catering trucks and any facility that dispenses food to the public. This information includes name and address of the food facility, identification of any major or minor violations, and date of last inspection.

This data is updated Sunday of every week.

Search By:

Restaurant Name:



OR

Address:



 Tips for Searching:
  • When searching by restaurant name, you can enter a partial name -- entering any portion of the restaurant name. 
  • When searching by address, you can enter  any portion of the address starting with the location number  or street name.
  • If entering the full name or address of the restaurant, please be careful to enter the name/address correctly in order to return results.

Major: Poses an immediate risk to public health and warrant immediate closure of the food establishment or immediate correction.

Minor: Does not pose an immediate risk to public health, but warrants correction.

***An "X" below major or minor indicates a violation.
***An "-" below major or minor indicates that the site has not been inspected to date.
